# ============================================================
# .trivyignore — Accepted CVE suppressions for Trivy
# ============================================================
# CVE-2026-22732 — Spring Security: security policy bypass and information
# disclosure (spring-security-web). Fixed in Spring Security 6.5.9, included
# in Spring Boot 3.5.x. Project is now on Spring Boot 3.5.14 — suppression
# retained as belt-and-suspenders pending confirmation from next Trivy run.
# Remove after next clean scan confirms the CVE no longer appears.
CVE-2026-22732
# CVE-2026-22739 — Spring Cloud Config Server: path traversal via profile parameter.
# Fixed in spring-cloud-config-server 4.3.2 (Spring Cloud 2025.x train).
# Project is now on Spring Cloud 2025.0.0 — suppression retained pending
# confirmation from next Trivy run. Remove after next clean scan.
CVE-2026-22739
# ── Go stdlib CVEs (gosu + Grafana binaries) ────────────────────────────────
# These CVEs are in Go standard library code compiled into gosu and Grafana
# binaries. They are NOT present in our Java Spring Boot service images.
#
# For gosu (postgres:15-alpine / redis:alpine):
#   The gosu maintainers confirm these CVEs do not apply because gosu does
#   not invoke the affected code paths (net/mail, html/template, httputil,
#   HTTP/2 transport). Reference: github.com/tianon/gosu/issues/104.
#
# For Grafana (grafana/grafana:11.6-security-01, third-party monitoring):
#   Grafana is a monitoring dependency, not part of the application attack
#   surface. Accepted upstream pending Grafana release with Go ≥ 1.26.3.
#
# CVE-2026-33811 — net: CNAME double-free/DoS via long CNAME response (cgo DNS).
#   gosu: does not make cgo DNS queries.
#   Java images: not affected (JVM DNS, not Go net).
CVE-2026-33811
# CVE-2026-33814 — golang.org/x/net: HTTP/2 SETTINGS_MAX_FRAME_SIZE=0 infinite loop.
#   gosu: does not use HTTP/2 transport.
#   Java images: not affected (use Netty/Tomcat, not Go x/net).
CVE-2026-33814
# CVE-2026-39820 — net/mail: ParseAddress/ParseAddressList/ParseDate excessive CPU.
#   gosu: does not parse RFC 5322 email addresses.
CVE-2026-39820
# CVE-2026-39836 — net: panic in Dial/LookupPort on NUL byte (Windows only).
#   Containers run on Linux Alpine; Windows code path is unreachable.
CVE-2026-39836
# CVE-2026-42499 — net/mail: consumePhrase quadratic DoS.
#   gosu: does not parse email headers.
CVE-2026-42499
# CVE-2026-27142 — html/template: URL not escaped in meta content attribute (XSS).
#   gosu: does not render HTML templates.
#   Grafana: fix requires rebuild with Go ≥ 1.26.3; accepted upstream.
CVE-2026-27142
# CVE-2026-39825 — net/http/httputil: ReverseProxy forwards invisible query params.
#   gosu: does not use httputil.ReverseProxy.
#   Grafana: accepted upstream.
CVE-2026-39825
# CVE-2026-39826 — html/template: script type="" escaper bypass (XSS).
#   gosu: does not render HTML templates.
#   Grafana: accepted upstream.
CVE-2026-39826
# ── Spring Cloud Config ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CVE-2026-41002 — Spring Cloud Config Server TOCTOU on Git clone base dir.
#   config-service is internal-only (not routed through API gateway, T-CFG-01).
#   Protected by HTTP Basic Auth (T-CFG-03). No external exposure.
#   Affected: spring-cloud-config-server 5.x. Fix pending Spring Cloud 2025.x patch.
CVE-2026-41002
# Format: one CVE-ID per line, with a comment explaining the
# justification — mirrors the approach used in
# config/dependency-check/suppressions.xml for OWASP DC.
# ============================================================
